DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Lymphocyte Outcome Lower Limit of Normal Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The lowest value of the range related the results of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for lymphocyte, a type of white blood cell that has a number of roles in the immune system, including the production of antibodies and other substances that fight infection and diseases.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related the results of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for lymphocyte, a type of white blood cell that has a number of roles in the immune system, including the production of antibodies and other substances that fight infection and diseases.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: (LIM-fo-site) A type of white blood cell. Lymphocytes have a number of roles in the immune system, including the production of antibodies and other substances that fight infection and diseases.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: White blood cells formed in the body's lymphoid tissue. The nucleus is round or ovoid with coarse, irregularly clumped chromatin while the cytoplasm is typically pale blue with azurophilic (if any) granules. Most lymphocytes can be classified as either T or B (with subpopulations of each); those with characteristics of neither major class are called null cells.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: the lowest value of the range of statistical characteristics that are supposed to represent accepted standard, non-pathological pattern for particular laboratory result or other quantitative parameter.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: The bottom of the normal range for a particular laboratory result.:A numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed.
